02/03/2003
NEUM, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- An expert commission on the demarcation of the border between Croatia and BiH met on Friday (28 February) to discuss issues related to implementation of an agreement on the state border.
They also reviewed the Agreement on Cross-Border Traffic, which is to be signed this week, and three annexes to the Agreement on Common Locations for Border Crossings.
In other news, Croatian Foreign Minister Tonino Picula will visit Sarajevo on Tuesday.
He will spend two days in BiH, meeting with his counterpart Mladen Ivanic and other top officials.
(HINA - 28/02/03)
